                     <h2>WHAT IS IN NATURAL FLAVORS & EXTRACTS?</h2>
                     <p>Nature's Flavors' premium natural flavor extracts are made from the finest ingredients available. All of our natural flavor extracts are sourced from natural ingredients and never have artificial ingredients or additional sweeteners. “The Flavor Guy” shops the world over for the purest and most unique natural and organic raw materials to bring you new and innovative flavorings and extracts. The unique flavor profiles of our natural extracts and flavorings will tantalize your taste buds!</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
               <div class="block d-flex flex-wrap">
                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>WHAT IS A NATURAL FLAVOR EXTRACT?</h2>
                     <p>Our extracts are water-soluble flavors made in a base of natural ethyl alcohol. These all-natural <%= link_to "flavor extracts", (Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Flavor Extracts").present? ? seo_url(Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Flavor Extracts")): '/')  %> and <%= link_to "organic flavoring extracts", (Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Organic Flavor Extracts").present? ? seo_url(Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Organic Flavor Extracts")): '/')  %> are food-grade, Kosher, vegan, and gluten-free. They are best used in clear beverages, dairy products, and applications where you don't want to disturb the clarity or translucency.</p>
                     <p>Our natural flavor extracts are of comparable strength with our <%= link_to "flavor concentrates", (Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Flavor Concentrates").present? ? seo_url(Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Flavor Concentrates")): '/')  %> and <%= link_to "flavor oils", (Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Flavor Oils").present? ? seo_url(Spree::Taxon.find_by_name("Flavor Oils")): '/')  %>. You will need to test the amount of the extract and flavoring to achieve the perfect strength for flavoring your recipe, but once you finish, you will be happy with the results.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
               <div class="block d-flex flex-wrap">
                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>WHY USE A NATURAL FLAVOR EXTRACT INSTEAD OF A FLAVOR CONCENTRATE?</h2>
                     <p>Nature’s Flavors’ natural flavor extracts and natural flavor concentrates are very similar. They are both all-natural and water-soluble products. The difference is that flavor concentrates have a cloudy or opaque look to them, whereas most natural extracts are clear*. This physical property is due to the base that these flavors are set in.</p>
                     <p>If your final application needs to be clear, then we recommend a natural flavor extract. Flavor concentrates are also more heat stable than extracts, so for baking, you might want to look at concentrates. Flavor extracts are in an alcohol base and will affect the freezing point of any recipe you put them into, while flavoring concentrates will not. *The few flavoring extracts that are not clear are mentioned on their product pages.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>

               <div class="block d-flex flex-wrap">
