                     <h2>WHAT ARE THE BEST USES OF NATURAL FLAVOR EXTRACTS?</h2>
                     <p>At Nature’s Flavors, our extracts and flavorings can be used in baking and clear beverages. The properties of natural flavor extracts include the following:</p>
                     <ul>
                        <li>Highly concentrated</li>
                        <li>Clear liquids</li>
                        <li>Water-based or alcohol-based only</li>
                        <li>High heat-stable</li>
                        <li>Alcohol bakes out at high temperatures</li>
                        <li>Ingredients - ethyl alcohol, natural and organic flavor</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>Caterers, restaurant chefs, home bakers, product manufacturers, brewers, and more will love using our natural flavorings and extracts to enhance the flavor profile of their desserts, culinary creations, alcoholic beverages, or products.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
               <div class="block d-flex flex-wrap">
                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>STARTING USAGE FOR FLAVORINGS & EXTRACTS</h2>
                     <p>A good rule for starting usage is .25% by weight. Finding the perfect amount of a natural flavor extract for your recipe is an art form and requires practice! First, start with a small amount of our natural extracts and flavorings, such as .25% (up to 1%) of your vanilla extract or preferred flavor. Taste the vanilla flavor in the finished dough or ice cream. If the flavor tastes good and dissipates after three to five seconds, it's perfect!</p>
                     <p>Note: if this is a baked product and it has not been baked, you will need to add 10% more natural flavor extracts to compensate for the loss of flavor during baking. When making and freezing ice cream, it is also possible that the natural extract will become diluted due to the whipping of air into the product from the ice cream machine, and you may need to add additional flavor extract.</p>
                  </div>
